#Purpose of Web3Skills in CryptoVoxels

The goal is a collective of applications and utilities and things that know how to operate in a system.

First, gather all core components needed to build a blockchain; things like a database networking a transaction queue consensus engine, and a library of runtime modules.

The runtime is something that describes what the blockchain transactions do. Technically speaking, it is the state transition function of that blockchain; the brains of that blockchain.

It defines the rules that are legal from one block transition to the next block, specifically how the state can literally transition. 

Now, design your own runtime modules and with a module library that will become become a part of a larger application ecosystem where there are other developers building all these open source runtime modules. 

Blockchain developers pick and choose the different functionality and logic and add it to blockchain and launch it.

It's getting easier than today to be able to build a blockchain with a substrate system. 

A balances module describes the functionality of a token on may be on this blockchain and if a smart contract is needed, just need to add the contracts module. If you want to add modules, make changes, or add features use the upgrade process as long as you get the governance body to approve it.

Literally, build a blockchain in minutes.

Substrate is powered by web assembly in terms of how the logic of the block chain is encoded. Parachains are encoded to serve as a useful launching off point for the greater parent network. 

Parachains are linchpins for developers and specialists in specific fields like machine learning or data science because they can get up and running their processes very quickly. 

It doesn't matter if it is a relay chain, a parachain that is connecting to these relay chains, or if you are running a chain somewhere on your own.
